cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper deals with zero-shot learning using class names and attributes, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed approach involves discriminative learning of word representations, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also involves text-only training, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
